WEBVTT

00:01.006 --> 00:03.976
<i>Previously on Transformers Prime...</i>

00:04.045 --> 00:07.513
Four sets of coordinates from
Alpha Trion remain encrypted.

00:07.582 --> 00:11.283
<i>It is logical to conclude that
each corresponds to the location</i>

00:11.352 --> 00:13.219
<i>of one of the Omega keys.</i>

00:16.590 --> 00:17.523
Scrap!

00:17.592 --> 00:21.594
It appears identical to the
one taken from me by Optimus Prime.

00:21.662 --> 00:24.263
Pieces of a larger puzzle, perhaps.

00:26.300 --> 00:30.970
Alpha Trion said we need all four
keys to restore Cybertron, remember?

00:31.038 --> 00:34.006
We just need to hang on to the
one we have, find a way to get

00:34.075 --> 00:35.507
the others back from Megatron.

00:35.576 --> 00:39.144
The final entry has been decoded.

00:39.213 --> 00:43.782
The coordinates are forming an image.

00:43.851 --> 00:45.150
Smokescreen?

00:45.219 --> 00:49.622
Prime's latest recruit is the
final relic of Iacon!

00:52.759 --> 00:54.627
No!

00:55.628 --> 00:58.628
<b>2x23 - Inside Job</b>

01:02.336 --> 01:04.703
Wakey, wakey.

01:04.772 --> 01:07.640
What?!

01:11.711 --> 01:16.715
If you're looking for your
Phase Shifter, finders keepers.

01:16.784 --> 01:19.051
<i>Enough prattling, Knockout!</i>

01:19.120 --> 01:22.921
Hand me the final Iacon relic ...
now.

01:22.990 --> 01:27.326
Yeah, I can't really help you.
That's the only one I was packing.

01:27.395 --> 01:29.328
Soundwave.

01:33.334 --> 01:34.900
You got the wrong guy, chief.

01:34.969 --> 01:38.504
Optimus Prime's the one who can
decode the Iacon database.

01:38.572 --> 01:41.440
Ah, but you misunderstand.

01:41.509 --> 01:45.177
The final entry has been
decoded by us!

01:45.246 --> 01:50.199
And according to our findings,
it would appear I do indeed

01:50.200 --> 01:52.117
have the right guy.

01:52.121 --> 01:56.624
The question is, what is it
that you are still packing?

01:59.030 --> 02:02.799
Why, hidden treasure, of course!

02:07.617 --> 02:10.616
